content:
Little freaking out; 
I finished Shiki mere minutes ago, i'm still in shock. The ending, it was perfect! Definitely not lacking, I think it fit the story line perfectly, so look forward to that if you are looking to watch this anime! The art was one of my favorite things about this anime, the vampire eyes were beautiful! The little girl vampire and mother figures eyes were stunning as well! 
Actual review; 
This animes' story line was perfect. The characters had nice back stories and were very relatable.It shows the insanity of an epidimic, and their actions seemed very likely of happening. It was realistic,but still had that 'creepy, mystical, vampire feel to it!' This isn't a stereotypical vampire anime, I assure you- there's not much romance, their isn't a thousand guys fawning over a girl- there's none of that. Though, if you're into that, their is megumi, a petite girl with pink hair that actually is quite scary later on in Shiki. \n\n
Enjoy this anime, It's for sure one of my favorites!   \n
